<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFEE6A51FD2A91521B03B21F" pageId="21" pageNumber="779" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFEE6A51FD2A91521B03B21F" blockId="21.[725,1318,1724,2151]" lastBlockId="21.[113,1321,2158,3494]" pageId="21" pageNumber="779">
Pipustrellusjavanicus has included 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEE6A51FB6791521B26BC1E" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[1179,1318,1803,1836]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="779" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="abramus">P. abramus</taxonomicName>
as a subspecies, but they are now regarded as distinct species based on morphology. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEE6A51FD2A91D81DE6BC90" authority="(Gray, 1838)" box="[726,998,1921,1954]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipustrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="779" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="javanicus">Piprstrellus javanicus</taxonomicName>
was previously known as P. tralatitius, which is regarded as a nomen dubium (dubious name). Populations in the 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFEE6A51FCCA91AE1DD1B32A" box="[822,977,2039,2072]" name="Philippines" pageId="21" pageNumber="779">Philippines</collectingCountry>
might represent two or more cryptic species, indicated by clear separation between large and small variants across the islands. There might be a number of species currently recognized under 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEE6A51FB149E371ED3B385" authority="(Gray, 1838)" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipustrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="779" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="javanicus">P. javanicus</taxonomicName>
throughoutits distribution. Subspecies camortae, babu, and peguensis have been considered distinct species, but they are considered subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEE6A51FC0D9EE41A8AB3EC" authority="(Gray, 1838)" box="[1009,1162,2237,2270]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipustrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="779" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="javanicus">P.javanicus</taxonomicName>
here based on morphology. Specimens previously attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEE6A51FCAD9EBC1DEEB234" authority="(Gray, 1838)" box="[849,1006,2277,2310]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipustrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="779" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="javanicus">P. javanicus</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFEE6A51FBB49EBC1AEDB234" box="[1096,1261,2277,2310]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="21" pageNumber="779">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
are now considered to have been misidentified 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEE6A51FD379F551D7FB21F" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[715,895,2316,2349]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="779" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="coromandra">P. coromandra</taxonomicName>
. Five subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
